SIMPLE: dissolved
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dissolved
<hw>dissolved</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>changed from a solid
to a liquid state by increase of temperature; melted. Opposite of
<ant>unmelted</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> liquefied, liquified, melted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>sundered by divorce, separation, or desertion; -- of
social bonds and relations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>diffused into a liquid of differing chemical
composition, forming a stable solution; -- said of chemical
substances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dissolvent</ent>⟦br⟧
